lobes","Superior temporal and lateral parietal regions","Occipital and inferior temporal regions","Medial temporal and inferior frontal regions"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanteromedial surface of cerebral hemisphere\u003C/strong\u003E is supplied by the anterior cerebral artery. This includes the medial portions of the frontal lobe (including supplementary motor area) and the superior medial portion of the parietal lobe.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent territories supplied by other cerebral arteries:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateral surface of frontal and parietal lobes\u003C/strong\u003E - This region is supplied by the middle cerebral artery\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuperior temporal and lateral parietal regions\u003C/strong\u003E - These areas are primarily supplied by the middle cerebral artery\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOccipital and inferior temporal regions\u003C/strong\u003E - These areas are supplied by the posterior cerebral artery\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedial temporal and inferior frontal regions\u003C/strong\u003E - The medial temporal lobe is supplied by the posterior cerebral artery, while the inferior frontal region is supplied by the middle cerebral artery\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the vascular territories of cerebral arteries is crucial for predicting the effects of cerebrovascular accidents affecting different vessels.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The anterior cerebral artery supplies the anteromedial surface of the cerebral hemisphere including the medial frontal lobe and superior medial parietal lobe.","The anterior cerebral artery is one of three major paired arteries that supply the cerebrum, along with the middle and posterior cerebral arteries."],"references":["Tahir RA, Haider S, Kole M, Griffith B, Marin H. Anterior Cerebral Artery: Variant Anatomy and Pathology. J Vasc Interv Neurol. 2019 May;10(3):16-22. PMID: 31308866; PMCID: PMC6613480.","Sibiya G, Omotoso BR, Harrichandparsad R, Lazarus L. Exploring the anatomical configurations of the cerebral arteries in a cohort of South African patients. Sci Rep. 2024 Mar 13;14(1):6060. doi: 10.1038/s41598-024-56767-y. PMID: 38480803; PMCID: PMC10937655.","Makowicz G, Poniatowska R, Lusawa M. Variants of cerebral arteries - anterior circulation. Pol J Radiol. 2013 Jul;78(3):42-7. doi: 10.12659/PJR.889403. PMID: 24115959; PMCID: PMC3789932.","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51117"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16556"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51117","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51117"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-26T17:11:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T14:31:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9247"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65678"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type"